omist.com/2015/11/19/108-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(497,1,'2016-01-19 17:27:20','2016-01-19 17:27:20','Stanley Pignal is the South Asia business and finance correspondent, based in Mumbai. In his previous role as Finance Correspondent he covered hedge funds, private equity, insurance and other institutional investors. He joined in October 2012 from the Financial Times, where he covered the European Union out of Brussels during the euro-zone crisis before returning to London to write about private equity. Mr Pignal also spent time in his native France to cover the banking, retail and luxury sectors. Prior to the FT Mr Pignal worked in corporate finance, analysing investment opportunities in the energy sector.','Stanley Pignal','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-autosave-v1','','','2016-01-19 17:27:20','2016-01-19 17:27:20','',131,'http://mediadirectory.economist.com/2015/11/19/131-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(498,1,'2015-11-19 19:56:13','2015-11-19 19:56:13','Stanley Pignal is The Economist\'s Banking Editor, based in London. In his previous role as Finance Correspondent he covered hedge funds, private equity, insurance and other institutional investors. He joined in October 2012 from the Financial Times, where he covered the European Union out of Brussels during the euro-zone crisis before returning to London to write about private equity. Mr Pignal also spent time in his native France to cover the banking, retail and luxury sectors. Prior to the FT Mr Pignal worked in corporate finance, analysing investment opportunities in the energy sector.','Stanley Pignal','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-revision-v1','','','2015-11-19 19:56:13','2015-11-19 19:56:13','',131,'http://mediadirectory.economist.com/2015/11/19/131-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(499,1,'2015-11-19 19:56:57','2015-11-19 19:56:57','Stanley Pignal is The Economist\'s Banking Editor, based in London. In his previous role as Finance Correspondent he covered hedge funds, private equi