INSERT INTO `econ_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES (52,'BLUEBEARD. Brave Warrior; Brutal Psychopath, our recently published book, is the true tale of the hero of the Hundred Years War and Joan of Arc\'s protector on the battlefield. When he could not save Joan from being burned to death by the English enemy, he cracked becoming the notorious serial killer of children nicknamed Bluebeard. The book explores the reason for his unraveling and equates his mental problems with those facing today\'s returning soldiers.'),(60,'Dear Mr. Curr,\r\n\r\nMy name is Justin Katz and I am a student at Yale University, where I am an Associate Editor of Yale\'s political magazine, The Politic. We frequently feature interviews with public officials, scholars, and authors, and I am writing to you today because I am wondering if one of our staff writers could speak with you over the phone for an interview. We would love to discuss your career in journalism, your take on the current US economic climate, and maybe some of your favorite bands.\r\n\r\nHere\'s a little background on our magazine:\r\n\r\nThe Politic is Yale\'s undergraduate political publication. Since 1947, we have been an outlet for the politically inclined on Yale\'s campus, with past Editors-in-Chief including Fareed Zakaria, Gideon Rose and Robert Kagan. We publish four times a year, featuring long-form, investigative articles. We pride ourselves in speaking with this country\'s—and the world\'s—foremost public servants, policy makers, and intellectuals. In the past, The Politic has interviewed President Obama, Secretary Kerry, President Zedillo of Mexico, and so many more. We recently concluded the largest and most rewarding project in our history, interviewing over 100 United States Ambassadors in a series entitled \"Diplomatic Discourse,\" which has received international attention, from the U.S. Department of State to media outlets worldwide.\r\n\r\nWe would be grateful for any amount of time that you could offer in the next month or so - we realize how busy your schedule is. I look forward to hearing back from you if this is possible, and I hope you are having a great week.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nJustin Katz\r\n\r\n— \r\nJustin Katz\r\nEzra Stiles College ‘18\r\nYale University \r\n(919) 943-5017'),(68,'Dear Mr. Lucas,\r\n\r\nMy name is Justin Katz and I am a student at Yale University, where I am an Associate Editor of Yale\'s political magazine, The Politic. We frequently feature interviews with public officials, scholars, and authors, and I am writing to you today because I am wondering if one of our staff writers could speak with you over the phone for an interview. We would love to discuss your career in journalism, your time at The Economist, and maybe even some of your favorite bands.\r\n\r\nHere\'s a little background on our magazine:\r\n\r\nThe Politic is Yale\'s undergraduate political publication. Since 1947, we have been an outlet for the politically inclined on Yale\'s campus, with past Editors-in-Chief including Fareed Zakaria, Gideon Rose and Robert Kagan. We publish four times a year, featuring long-form, investigative articles. We pride ourselves in speaking with this country\'s—and the world\'s—foremost public servants, policy makers, and intellectuals. In the past, The Politic has interviewed President Obama, Secretary Kerry, President Zedillo of Mexico, and so many more. We recently concluded the largest and most rewarding project in our history, interviewing over 100 United States Ambassadors in a series entitled \"Diplomatic Discourse,\" which has received international attention, from the U.S. Department of State to media outlets worldwide.\r\n\r\nWe would be grateful for any amount of time that you could offer in the next month or so - we realize how busy your schedule is. I look forward to hearing back from you if this is possible, and I hope you are having a great week.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nJustin Katz\r\n\r\n— \r\nJustin Katz\r\nEzra Stiles College ‘18\r\nYale University \r\n(919) 943-5017'),(76,'Dear Ms. McElvoy,\r\n\r\nMy name is Justin Katz and I am a student at Yale University, where I am an Associate Editor of Yale\'s political magazine, The Politic. We frequently feature interviews with public officials, scholars, and authors, and I am writing to you today because I am wondering if one of our staff writers could speak with you over the phone for an interview. We would love to discuss your career in journalism, your tenure at The Economist, and maybe even some of your favorite bands.\r\n\r\nHere\'s a little background on our magazine:\r\n\r\nThe Politic is Yale\'s undergraduate political publication. Since 1947, we have been an outlet for the politically inclined on Yale\'s campus, with past Editors-in-Chief including Fareed Zakaria, Gideon Rose and Robert Kagan. We publish four times a year, featuring long-form, investigative articles. We pride ourselves in speaking with this country\'s—and the world\'s—foremost public servants, policy makers, and intellectuals. In the past, The Politic has interviewed President Obama, Secretary Kerry, President Zedillo of Mexico, and so many more. We recently concluded the largest and most rewarding project in our history, interviewing over 100 United States Ambassadors in a series entitled \"Diplomatic Discourse,\" which has received international attention, from the U.S. Department of State to media outlets worldwide.\r\n\r\nWe would be grateful for any amount of time that you could offer in the next month or so - we realize how busy your schedule is. I look forward to hearing back from you if this is possible, and I hope you are having a great week.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nJustin Katz\r\n\r\n— \r\nJustin Katz\r\nEzra Stiles College ‘18\r\nYale University \r\n(919) 943-5017'),(84,'Dear Ms. Beddoes,\r\n\r\nMy name is Justin Katz and I am a student at Yale University, where I am an Associate Editor of Yale\'s political magazine, The Politic. We frequently feature interviews with public officials, scholars, and authors, and I am writing to you today because I am wondering if one of our staff writers could speak with you over the phone for an interview. We would love to discuss your career in journalism, your tenure at The Economist, your take on global macroeconomic developments, and maybe even some of your favorite bands.\r\n\r\nHere\'s a little background on our magazine:\r\n\r\nThe Politic is Yale\'s undergraduate political publication. Since 1947, we have been an outlet for the politically inclined on Yale\'s campus, with past Editors-in-Chief including Fareed Zakaria, Gideon Rose and Robert Kagan. We publish four times a year, featuring long-form, investigative articles. We pride ourselves in speaking with this country\'s—and the world\'s—foremost public servants, policy makers, and intellectuals. In the past, The Politic has interviewed President Obama, Secretary Kerry, President Zedillo of Mexico, and so many more. We recently concluded the largest and most rewarding project in our history, interviewing over 100 United States Ambassadors in a series entitled \"Diplomatic Discourse,\" which has received international attention, from the U.S. Department of State to media outlets worldwide.\r\n\r\nWe would be grateful for any amount of time that you could offer in the next month or so - we realize how busy your schedule is. I look forward to hearing back from you if this is possible, and I hope you are having a great week.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nJustin Katz\r\n\r\n— \r\nJustin Katz\r\nEzra Stiles College ‘18\r\nYale University \r\n(919) 943-5017'),(100,'Alexandra Suich, \r\n\r\nGood afternoon. I am writing to you today in regard to your most recent issues that were published in November. My name is John Bat, and I am a journalism student at the University of Missouri. The interest area within my major is Arts & Culture - Magazine. Currently, I am taking an independent study class focusing on identifying how editors make decisions about how their publication\'s stories are written for unique niche audiences. One of the magazines I reviewed was The Economist, specifically the October 31st-November 6th issue on the “Trust Machine.” I cannot turn in a holistic paper to my supervisor (Laura Johnston, editor at the Columbia Missourian) on my findings until I talk to an editor at your publication. I was wondering if you or one of your editors, sometime this week or next, could help me answer some basic questions about the magazine. \r\n\r\nPlease feel free to contact me at anytime. My schedule is flexible! \r\n\r\nMuch thanks,\r\n\r\nJohn'),(108,'Dear Sir,\r\nPlease let me know if The Economist may be interested in direct photojournalistic news service.\r\nYou may see some latest shots from demonstration held on Dec.03\'15 in the defense of  polish Constitution in front of Constitutional Tribunal in Warsaw, Poland at www.fotonova.pl/pictures/result?phrase=kruszewski&search-way=keywords\r\n\r\nThank you for your response,\r\nBest regards,\r\nAndrzej Kruszewski'),(116,'Dominic,\r\n\r\nHope you are well. I am wondering whether you might be available for an interview over the Christmas period about Black Dragon River.\r\n\r\nI am back doing some interviews in London for our Last Word profiles.\r\n\r\nI am looking for about 40 minutes. \r\n\r\nI did something similar with John Micklethwait last year.\r\n \r\nbest regards,\r\n\r\nAndrew\r\n\r\nAndrew Moody\r\n \r\nSenior correspondent,\r\nChina Daily,\r\n15 Huixin Dongjie,\r\nChaoyang District,\r\nBEIJING 100029,\r\nCHINA.\r\n(0086) 1064995194 (office)\r\n(0086) 13552054360 (mob)\r\n(0086) 1084833689  (home)'),(124,'Dominic,\r\n\r\nHope you are well. I am wondering whether you might be available for an interview over the Christmas period about Black Dragon River.\r\n\r\nI am back doing some interviews in London for our Last Word profiles.\r\n\r\nI am looking for about 40 minutes. \r\n\r\nI did something similar with John Micklethwait last year.\r\n \r\nbest regards