iously subject to change) but to give you an idea of the calibre of the investors, together with their investor profiles.\r\n\r\nMike Levshin, Senior PM – Ontario Teachers \r\nJean-Rene Adam, CIO - Hexavest Canada\r\nAsad Mawjee, Senior Analyst - Lord Abbett \r\nStephen Austin, Senior Analyst - Lockheed Martin\r\n\r\nI look forward to hearing from you soon, much appreciate your assistance.\r\n\r\nKind regards\r\nVanessa\r\n\r\n\r\nVanessa Easlea | Corporate Access Origination - Europe\r\nMacquarie Securities Group | Macquarie Capital (Europe) Ltd.\r\nRopemaker Place, 28 Ropemaker Street, London, EC2Y 9HD\r\nT +44 20 3037 4446 | M +44 7909 690143 | F +44 20 3037 4307 | vanessa.easlea@macquarie.com'),(6045,'Regarding this item http://www.economist.com/news/americas/21714403-he-may-encounter-roadblocks-torontos-mayor-tries-improve-transport\r\nIt\'s laden with errors. If you\'re looking for a veteran journalist who can write accurately about the Toronto situation, let me know (I\'m semi-retired from The Globe and Mail, Toronto Star, Toronto Sun and Financial Post.)'),(6053,'Dear Mr Nuttall,\r\n\r\nI am writing to you on behalf of the Bellevue Programme (http://www.bosch-stiftung.de/content/language1/html/975.asp), initiated by the German Federal President and the Robert Bosch Foundation. As the seminar leader of the Bellevue Programme I would like to approach you and ask you for your support. Before going into detail, let me briefly describe the concept of the Bellevue Programme:\r\n\r\nEach year, up to 12 highly qualified junior and mid-career civil servants from key government authorities in France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Poland, Portugal, Slovenia and Spain get selected in a competitive process for the Bellevue Programme. The programme promotes the participants’ professional, intercultural and European policy competencies and hence their capacity to assume leadership positions in their home institution.  \r\n\r\nThe Bellevue Programme is deliberately not bilateral, but a rotating exchange between the partner countries that is designed to foster a pan-European network among public administrators over time. The duration, intensity and number of participating countries in the Bellevue Programme are unprecedented.\r\n\r\nThe programme was established in 2004 by the Robert Bosch Stiftung together with the German Federal President’s Office. It derives its name from Schloss Bellevue (Bellevue Palace), the official residence of the Federal President. The Robert Bosch Stiftung funds the programme and is responsible for its implementation. \r\n\r\nThe EU Seminar of the Bellevue Programme is going to take place March 6th - 15th in Brussels and in Strasbourg. In its course the participants of the programme will meet representatives of the different European institutions in the two cities and discuss current issues, trends and perspectives of the specific sphere the respective speaker is working in. \r\n\r\nWe would be honoured if you would agree to give a presentation of about an hour length including discussion on \'Populism on the rise in Europe\' on March 12, 2017 in the afternoon at the Hotel Silken Berlaymont, Blvd. Charlemagne 11/19 in Brussels. If you have any questions or if the proposed date does not correspond with your time schedule please do not hesitate to contact me. \r\n\r\nI am looking forward to receiving your reply.\r\n\r\nDr. Monika Gonser\r\nSeminar leader\r\nBellevue Programme'),(6061,'I’m writing from the Wikimedia Foundation, the non-profit that operates Wikipedia and sister projects including Wikimedia Commons. Next week, our Executive Director Katherine Maher will be in London, and I wanted to gauge your interest in an introductory meeting. Katherine would be happy to discuss a broad range of topics, but we thought you might be interested in one issue in particular: how the proposed EU copyright reform before the Legal Affairs committee could impact free knowledge projects like Wikipedia.\r\n\r\nCopyright policy matters to Wikipedia: all content on the platform is freely licensed (like Creative Commons) or in the public domain. As they contribute content, volunteer editors respect copyright laws and diligently monitor the platforms to ensure that the content uploaded by others complies with laws. Unfortunately, the public domain is threatened by the creation of new rights for authors and traditional rightsholders. We would love to see the next generation of copyright laws protect the public interest and the public’s ability to freely share information and knowledge.\r\n\r\nWe have specific concerns about a number of aspects of the currently proposed changes to the EU Copyright Directive. Katherine would be happy to speak to those with you, and discuss anything else that may be of interest.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you’re interested or have any questions. We hope to have the opportunity to discuss this important issue with you. \r\n\r\nThank you,\r\nJuliet \r\n\r\nEmail: jbarbara@wikimedia.org'),(6098,'Good Morning \r\n\r\nI’m a News Journalist of the Swiss Broadcasting Television. I’ll be in Davos during the World economic forum and, if possible, I would like to make an Interview with Miss Zanny Minton Beddoes about the economic future of the United States of America under Donald Trump’s presidency. \r\nWe will need 10 Minutes.\r\n\r\nIt could be possibile?\r\n\r\nThank you.\r\nBest Regards.\r\nDavide Paggi'),(6106,'On behalf of MediaLink Communications, I would like to ask about the availability and your permission to interview Executive Editor Daniel Franklin during his stay in Malta, for the \'The World in 2017\' event.\r\n\r\nThe interview will revolve around the change that the world is going through in recent years, being in topic with your theme in Malta.\r\n\r\nThanks.'),(6129,'January 17th 2017,\r\n\r\nDear Mr. Avent,\r\n\r\nI’m writing to you today, as the Manager of Operations of the Henry George School of Social Science (www.hgsss.org).   O