 This year we proudly celebrate the 70th anniversary of Journal\'s continuous existence as one of the most respected voices of the Columbia community.\r\n\r\nThe interview would consist of approximately ten questions.  We would prefer to conduct it through email or Skype.  Journal’s interviews are presented verbatim.  Before the publication, the interview would be submitted to Ms. Minton Beddoes for a personal authorization.  It would be published in the Spring 2017 issue of the Journal – in bookstores in May. \r\n\r\nWe at the Journal of International Affairs very much hope that Ms. Minton Beddoes accept this invitation.  Please let me know if there is any further information that I can provide to help Ms. Minton Beddoes make her decision.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nDjivo Djurovic\r\nFeatures Editor\r\nJournal of International Affairs\r\njia.sipa.columbia.edu \r\nColumbia University\r\n\r\n518-488-8987\r\ndjivo.djurovic@columbia.edu'),(6625,'My name is Lena Korallo. I am a freelance journalist and a documentary filmmaker. I am in the process of making a film about the immigration. Briefly, the idea is to explore what do people know about the immigration and if it is a threat to the UK. An important part of the film is experts view on the immigration and its impact on the UK\'s economy. I am Economist\'s reader for two years, and I greatly value your professionalism. I would like to ask for a short interview for my project.\r\nWhen it is ready, the documentary will be posted online on my personal website, my Youtube channel and a few documentary film festivals. You can find more information about me and my work on my LinkedIn profile (https://uk.linkedin.com/in/jelena-korallo-65634286) and my website (lena-korallo.squarespace.com ) \r\nIf you have any questions, please, feel free to ask.\r\n\r\nKind Regards,\r\n\r\nLena Korallo.'),(6641,'Hi, I\'m looking to speak to Ann Wroe about her experiences as an obituary editor, particularly to find out the most interesting non